The other night, I made roast chicken, mashed potatoes, and a saute of summer squash, red peppers, shallots, and tarragon. This was a perfect way to use up the leftover potatoes and sauteed veggies. I used more parmesan because I'm a cheese freak, and it was delicious!

Rating: 3
I halved this recipe, substituting bottled roasted red pepper and green onions for the peppers and onions called for. It made a nice quick supper for my toddler and me. Next time I make it, I will probably vary the types of vegetables I use, and will try adding small cubes of ham. This is one of those recipes you can have fun playing with.

