I was searching for a way to utilize left over mashed potatoes for breakfast and Wa-La!! This was it!! It was very delicious. And instead of an omlette, I made it into a casserole. I just combined everything and put it into a pan and baked it. And I just noticed tonight that someone else also used portobellos! Yummy, we all loved it.

Rating: 3
Even without the peppers (and with instant mashed potatoes)this was a very tasty, rich dish. I used portobello mushrooms. Yum! I assume the peppers would add even more dimension and less uniform heaviness to this dish. As it was, a little time consuming;would be even more so when using whole potatoes. A very delicious quiche-like brunch entree.